post_cb({"14244652": {"ParentId": "14244644", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>Because it is valid in C++ (and not valid in C).</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_14244644_14244652_0\">(C++11, 6.7p4) \"Constant initialization (3.6.2) of a block-scope\n              entity with static storage duration, if applicable, is performed before\n              its block is first entered. [...] Otherwise such a variable is\n              initialized the first time control passes through its declaration;\n              such a variable is considered initialized upon the completion of\n              its initialization.\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1119701", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "14244652", "Score": "19", "CreationDate": "2013-01-09T19:10:54.343", "LastActivityDate": "2013-01-09T19:10:54.343"}, "14244644": {"CommentCount": "4", "AcceptedAnswerId": "14244652", "CreationDate": "2013-01-09T19:10:05.073", "LastActivityDate": "2013-01-09T19:10:54.343", "PostTypeId": "1", "ViewCount": "156", "FavoriteCount": "0", "Title": "Why Declaration of static variable with non-constant does not give Error in g++", "Id": "14244644", "Score": "14", "Body": "<pre><code> int main ( )\n {\n       int a = 1 ;\n       static int b = a ;\n }\n</code></pre>\n<p>This piece of code gives error in <strong>gcc 4.3.2</strong> as</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_14244644_14244644_0\">error : initializer element is not constant.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>But it runs fine on <strong>g++ 4.3.2</strong>.\n Someone Please Explain why this is not giving error in g++ 4.3.2.</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c>", "OwnerUserId": "1729729", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_14244644_14244652_0": {"section_id": 3919, "quality": 0.9142857142857143, "length": 32}}, "n3337": {"so_14244644_14244652_0": {"section_id": 3779, "quality": 0.9142857142857143, "length": 32}}, "n4659": {"so_14244644_14244652_0": {"section_id": 4805, "quality": 0.5714285714285714, "length": 20}}}});